The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Tax break for parties

 New Delhi, Oct. 31 (PTI): The government today promulgated an ordinance exempting political parties and some charitable institutions that do not pay income-tax from the fringe benefit tax.

 The ordinance amended Section 115 (W) of the Income-tax Act to exempt registered political parties and companies registered under Section 25 of the Companies Act and Section 12 (AA) of the Income-Tax Act from the fringe tax, an official release said.

 The ordinance exempted inter-bank transactions from banking cash transaction tax by amending Chapter VII of the Finance Act, 2005.

 Section 10 of the Income-Tax Act has been amended to exempt notified persons specified income arising from international events in India approved by the recognised international body.




